NBA想空场比赛，但需面对每场2000万门票损失和众球星反对。
The NBA wants to play an empty game, but faces a loss of 20 million tickets per game and opposition from the stars.
李晓庄。
Li Xiaozhuang.
界面新闻                      。
Interface news.
界面新闻。
Interface news.
界面新闻是中国具有影响力的原创财经新媒体，只服务于独立思考的人群。
Interface News is an original and influential new financial media in China, serving only the people who think independently.
湖人球星詹姆斯表示不愿进行空场比赛。
Lakers star James says he does not want to play short.
（图片来源：Getty）记者：李晓庄“ 如果空场计划确定实行，球队每场比赛将损失约200万美元的门票收入。
(Photo: Getty) Journalist: Li Xiaozhuang will lose about two million dollars per game if the empty plans are confirmed.
”当地时间3月6日晚，联盟再次下发备忘录，要求各支球队做好包括“推迟比赛、进行空场（禁止观众入场）比赛”在内的多项准备。
On the night of March 6, the league issued a new memorandum asking teams to prepare for games that included "postponing the game and holding a free field match.
此外，联盟还要求各支球队在周二之前制定计划，以降低同球员互动的人员数量。
The league also wants teams to have plans in place by Tuesday to reduce the number of players they interact with.
目前，各媒体的记者已经被限制进入球队更衣室。
Media reporters have been restricted from entering the team's dressing room.
鹈鹕教练Alvin Gentry对空场比赛的计划并不感到惊讶，并认为联盟应该对疫情持谨慎态度。
Pelican coach Alvin Gentry wasn't surprised by plans for an empty game and said the alliance should be cautious about the outbreak.
实际上，在NBA发放此份备忘录之前，已经有球队对观赛球迷进行了引导。
In fact, before the NBA issued the memo, teams were already guiding the spectators.
当地时间3月6日，旧金山公共卫生部门建议推迟或取消非必要大型集会，其中就包括篮球比赛。
On March 6, San Francisco's public health department proposed postponing or canceling major non-essential rallies, including basketball games.
当天，勇士队发布公告，呼吁身体不适和体质较弱的球迷不要前往现场观看比赛。
On the same day, the Warriors issued a public notice, calling on the sick and weak fans not to go to the scene to watch the game.
在球场门口，勇士队张贴了疫情警示，以提醒观众病毒传播的风险。
In front of the stadium, the Warriors put up the alert to alert the audience to the risk of spreading the virus.
然而，并非所有人都接受空场比赛的安排。
However, not everyone accepts the arrangements for a free field match.
在随后几天的采访中，洛杉矶湖人队球星詹姆斯、凯尔特人球员肯巴·沃克等球员公开表示不愿进行空场比赛。
In interviews over the next few days, Los Angeles Lakers star James, Celtic player Kemba Walker and other players openly expressed their unwillingness to play in a short game.
詹姆斯说:“（空场）是不可能的。
"It's impossible," James said.
如果没有球迷，我不会打球的，（球迷）是我打球的目的。
If there were no fans, I wouldn't be playing. That's what I'm playing for.
”除了球员，球队高层也提出反对意见。
"In addition to the players, the team's top brass raised objections.
休斯顿火箭队老板Tilman Fertitta称，自己甚至愿意停赛一到两个星期，也不愿意进行空场比赛。
Houston Rockets owner Tilman Fertitta says he is even willing to suspend play for a week or two rather than play an empty game.
同时，Fertitta指出，在3月5日的比赛中，疫情引发的担忧并没有对上座率产生任何负面影响。
Meanwhile, Fertitta points out that in the March 5 race, concerns about the outbreak did not have any negative impact on attendance.
根据联盟的官方数据，当晚比赛的18055张门票售罄，缺席人数甚至少于平日。
That night 18,055 tickets were sold out and even fewer people were absent, according to the league's official figures.
正因此，Fertitta呼吁球迷保持冷静，不要盲目恐慌。
So Fertitta urged fans to remain calm and not to panic blindly.
无独有偶，NHL佛罗里达美洲豹队的老板Viola对Fertitta表示支持，认为空场比赛将会影响球迷与职业体育比赛的互动。
Similarly, NHL Florida Jaguar owner Viola told Fertitta that the game would affect fans' interaction with professional sports.
此外，在Twitter等社交媒体上，空场比赛因为缺少互动性、季票持有者遭受损失等原因遭到批评。
In addition, on social media such as Twitter, open-field games have been criticized for their lack of interactivity and the loss of season ticket holders.
有球迷毫不留情，直言这种行为将会毁了比赛。
Some fans showed no mercy, saying that such behavior would destroy the game.
经济收益是阻碍空场计划推行的主要原因。
Economic gain is the main reason for blocking the implementation of the empty space program.
根据估算，如果空场计划确定实行，球队每场比赛将损失约200万美元的门票收入，这个数字还不包括饮品、食物、球队周边等潜在收益。
It is estimated that the team will lose about $2 million per game if the empty plans are set to go ahead. That figure does not include potential benefits such as drinks, food and the team's surroundings.
同时，观众的减少也会影响相关产业的效益。
At the same time, the reduction in audience will also affect the efficiency of the relevant industries.
根据2011年的数据，在NBA停摆两周后，其球馆周边的饭店、旅店等服务业遭受了数亿美元的损失。
According to 2011 data, after a two-week hiatus in the NBA, hotels and other services around the stadium sustained hundreds of millions of dollars in losses.
但如果情况不断恶化，空场或许是得以降低损失的唯一手段。
But if things get worse, the empty space may be the only way to reduce losses.
根据NBA此前的方案，若真有球员感染，其整支球队都将被隔离。
Under the NBA's previous plan, if a player gets infected, the entire team will be quarantined.
甚至将造成整个联盟的停摆。
It could even bring down the entire alliance.
而对比门票收入，广告和电视网络转播才是盈利重头。
In contrast to ticket sales, advertising and television network transmissions are the most profitable.
价值不菲的转播合同、高昂的场馆租金，都无法让联盟放弃继续比赛的可能。
High-value broadcasting contracts and exorbitant venue rents will not allow the league to give up the possibility of continuing the competition.
